						               													<description>Have you ever dreamed about starting your own band and living the rock life? Party Bandimals gives you the experience of being the band manager with the important job of scouting out the best talent for your band of animals. You will be playing against other managers who are trying to add the best musical animals to their band, while trying to push the worst musicians to your band.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Party Bandimals is best for 2-4 players and takes about 15 minutes to play, but only minutes to learn! Do you have what it takes to make your band a success?&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Goal&amp;#10;In Party Bandimals, you play as the role of a band manager. Your goal is to be the first manager to assemble a band with 11 points. You get points by playing good members into your band but beware other players can play bad members into &amp;#10;your band lowering your score. If the cards run out the player with the highest score wins.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Setup&amp;#10;Deal each player 3 cards. Each player should discard any 'Play When Drawn' cards and draw back up to three cards. &amp;#10;The player who played an instrument last goes first.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;How to play&amp;#10;On your turn you must draw up to four cards and play one card.  If you draw a 'Play when drawn' card, it must be the card you play. Good members can only be played in your band and bad band members can only be played into another players band. Played cards are placed in front of you, thus forming your band, or in front of another player when adding bad band members to their band.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;&amp;mdash;description from the publisher&amp;#10;&amp;#10;</description>
